The young daughter of a rapper gunned down in a fatal nightclub shooting has lit a candle for her father during an emotion vigil just a few feet from where he died.

Glenn Thomas, known on stage as Doe B, was killed alongside young college student Kimberle Johnson who was celebrating her 21st birthday inside an Alabama bar.

Another reveller was critically wounded and is in intensive care while five others were also seriously injured when shots rang out in a packed Montgomery bar just before 1am Saturday morning.

Madison Thomas, 3, joined dozens of other mourners to lay flowers and light candles at the scene of the bloodbath.

