A third unidentified person is in the hospital with ‘life threatening’ injuries, a police spokesperson told MailOnline, declining to provide further details.

Centennial Bar and Grill, where the shooting occurred, was ordered closed by Montgomery Mayor Todd Strange for posing an ‘imminent threat to the public's safety,’ according to a published statement.

This was the second such attack at the club in the last year. A December 2012 shooting left six injured at the bar, then-named Rose Supper Club, according to WNCF.

